node.title: Data talk: Built a Data Mesh Architecture
node.description:
Register on the event website to receive joining link: https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2022060902

**Description:**
Data teams in large enterprise organizations are facing greater demand for data to satisfy a wide range of analytic use cases, yet they are challenged with providing access to all of their data across business units, regions, and cloud environments. In this webinar, learn how Enel Group worked with Agile Lab to implement Dremio as a data mesh solution for providing broad access to a unified view of their data, and how they use that architecture to enable a multitude of use cases.

In this session, you will learn:
\- How the silos development led to challenges with data growth\, data quality\, data sharing\, and data governance\. An example of data mesh paradigm adoption
\- How Agile Lab and Enel Group used Dremio to connect their disparate organizations across geographies and business units
\- Leveraging Dremio for data governance and multi\-cloud with Arrow Flight\.

node.title: ML Talk: Reasonable Scale Machine Learning
node.description:
Please complete registration on the event website to receive join link:
https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2022053116

**Description:**
Machine learning comes in many shapes and sizes but most of the conversation (around tools, techniques, division of labor) is dominated by a handful of companies, who do ML at a scale nobody else needs to. Of all the endless forms that companies outside of Big Tech can take, particularly interesting is a growing and underserved segment that is especially relevant for ML systems, known as reasonable scale companies, meaning reasonable along the axes of monetary impact, team size, data volume, and compute resources.

Jacopo and Hugo will discuss reasonable scale machine learning and what the majority of non-FAANG companies need to know in order to build out sophisticated ML functions, and we will also discuss what such machine learning actually looks like for businesses and practitioners alike, and what you can do to get started with reasonable scale ML today.

After attending, you‚Äôll know:

* What types of companies can benefit from reasonable scale machine learning (hint: most);
* What types of data, tools, and talent you need in order to build a sustainable ML function;
* Barriers to entry for reasonable scale machine learning, how you can get started today, and industry trends that will help you in your ML journey.

The fireside chat will be followed by an AMA with Jacopo and Hugo at slack.outerbounds.co.

Speakers:
Jacopo Tagliabue is Coveo's Director of A.I., where they combine product thinking and research-like curiosity to build better data-driven systems at scale.
Hugo Bowne-Anderson, Outerbounds‚Äô Head of Developer Relations

node.title: Tech Talk:  StarRocks vs ClickHouse, Apache Druid and Trino
node.description:
Register here to receive zoom link:
https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2022050517

StarRocks is an open source, next-gen sub-second MPP database for full analytics scenarios, including multi-dimensional analytics, real-time analytics and ad-hoc query. Many companies across various industries have deployed StarRocks in their online production environments, including Airbnb, JD.com, Tencent, and Trip.com.

Recently, StarRocks published an article stating that it got very good results on both SSB flat table and TPCH benchmarking, which outperforms ClickHouse, Apache Druid, and Trino.

In this talk, Peter Pang from StarRocks will discuss:
\-\- Intro to StarRocks? \(5 mins\)
\-\- Deep dive on StarRocks design\, query performance in wide\-table and multi\-table scenarios\. \(20 mins\)
\-\- Live demo \(20 mins\)
\-\- Q&A

node.title: Tech Talk: Natural Language Search for 2D and 3D Training Data
node.description:
Register here to receive joining link: https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2022050312

Description:
What is the easiest way of curating training data?

Instead of writing queries with precise syntax, you can just type what you‚Äôre looking for, such as ‚Äúa photo of an emergency vehicle.‚Äù If a 2D image is matched with a corresponding point cloud, you can explore that point cloud and its tags to see if it suits the ‚Äúedge case‚Äù you‚Äôre investigating to train your model to handle it.

Join us for an in-depth tech talk where we show you how to leverage a novel approach to data discovery. What we will cover in this talk:
\- No need to learn syntax: filter your dataset with plain old words
\- Slice and dice your 3D data with only a text search
\- Speed up your dataset creation pipeline\, even with challenging data types like 3D
\- See how you can unearth even unlabeled data with natural language

node.title: AWS AI/ML Series: Finding Cheaters In Online Games Using ML
node.description:
== Register to receive join link here ==
https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2022031618

We are partnering with AWS team to host a series of AI/ML tech seminars for the community. We will give away a few AWS credits ($20/each) during the event.

Description:
Cheating in online gaming is on the rise and cheaters are getting increasingly sophisticated at evading human and rule-based detection with their cheats. Machine Learning is seen as the solution which can identify suspicious patterns and adapt to changes in cheater behavior, however a solution like this is often complex to implement and manage, with dedicated data science teams required to operate it effectively.

In this session, learn how services like Amazon Fraud Detector and Amazon SageMaker can be easily implemented to detect cheaters in online mobile games without any prior AI or ML knowledge required!

* Intended audience: IT engineers/sysadmins/developers interested in learning about AI/ML .
* Level: Intermediate
